HEADWORD: Gownman
<hw>Gown"man</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>-men</plw>
<pr>(-men)</pr>.</plu> <def>One whose professional habit is a gown, as a
divine or lawyer, and particularly a member of an English university;
hence, a civilian, in distinction from a soldier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

